To determine steady state kinetic parameters for the substrate L-KYN, 50 μL reaction mixtures containing 10 ng/μL recombinant human KAT2, 1 mM α-KG, 100 μM PLP, 0.005% Tween 20, L-KYN at concentrations of 10, 5, 2.5, 1.25, 0.62, 0.31 and 0.15 mM and GL, GA or CBX or PF-04859989 at 4.5, 6.0 and 3.5 μM and 300 nM, respectively. Following incubation for 30 min at 37 °C, reactions were stopped by adding 3% perchloric acid at a 1:1 ratio. KYNA concentrations were measured using the same HPLC method as described above. Double reciprocal plots were used to determine types of inhibition. Competitive inhibition constants (Ki) for GL, GA and CBX were calculated using the global fit formula (GraphPad Prism v6.07)60,61 as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
